                    <p class="card-text">
                        An electroencephalogram (EEG) is a test that detects electrical activity in the brain using small metal discs (electrodes) attached to the scalp. Brain cells communicate via electrical impulses and are active all the time, even during sleep. This activity appears as waves on an EEG.
                    </p>
