                    <p class="card-text">
                        This study leverages an existing EEG database collected by Igor Zyma, Sergii Tukaev, and Ivan Seleznov, which includes EEG recordings of subjects performing mental arithmetic tasks. Each subject was evaluated under two conditions: a baseline (Normal) and while performing mathematical operations (Performing Operations). The sample is divided into two groups, one high-performing (Group "G") and one low-performing (Group "B"), providing a rich opportunity to explore the neurocognitive differences underlying various levels of mathematical ability.
                    </p>
